                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d662">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 Stam, John C./67: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-19T19:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 19, 1935—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 19—11:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>82. Reference Legation’s 81, February 18, 8 p.m., following telegram has been
                    received from Peck at Nanking: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“February 19, 2 p.m. My February 18, 5 p.m.,<note n="84"
                                xml:id="d662fn84">See <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> last
                            paragraph. <pb facs="0790" n="678" xml:id="pg_678"/> I delivered message
                            to Director Liu February 19, 11 a.m. and he said the Foreign Office
                            stated [it] would release the information.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
